transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Hi, yeah, I'd like to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: What's your name and date of birth?

Speaker 2: Yeah, Chris Chase, and my date of birth is October 4, 1966.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm looking at my website page that says Christopher, so maybe Christopher Chase.

Speaker 2: Okay, Christopher, and what's going on? Is it that you have enough supply at this time?

Speaker 1: Well, that and it's actually, I thought having that new ingredient would help, but it doesn't work for me.

Speaker 2: All I get is the side effects.

Speaker 1: So you shouldn't be getting side effects with the AGV. Do you have the pills with you at this moment?

Speaker 2: I do.

Speaker 1: Okay, can you take a look at them and let me know what's ingrained from the pills? Take a look at the pills.

Speaker 2: Yeah, hold on a second.

Speaker 1: It says AC339.

Speaker 2: Oh, that explains why you're getting side effects because it looks like they sent you the classic Viagra instead of the AGV Christopher.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So what I will go ahead and do is that I'll ask the pharmacy to reship your order at no additional cost to make up for that.

Speaker 1: And then I will also go ahead and pause your VIP. I'll pause it until April.

Speaker 2: That way you have enough time to use the supply that you currently have at the moment, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, so this one I should just dump it down the toilet or whatever?

Speaker 2: Yeah, go ahead and keep them or discard them. I mean, you're getting side effects, so you probably don't want to take them.

Speaker 1: So go ahead and just discard them. And then I will be asking the pharmacy to reship that order to you.

Speaker 2: And then I will also be pausing your VIP until April, okay?

Speaker 1: Sounds good.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, you're all set, Christopher. Have a good rest of your day, okay?

Speaker 1: You as well. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye.
